case_inclusion_criteria: individuals aged 1 year and older on the first day of the vaccination campaign who sought care for diarrhoea at participating health structures; who had three or more loose stools in the preceding 24 h; who had lived in the same residence during the preceding 2 weeks (within a 2 h drive of central Juba); and who had not visited a health facility for diarrhoea before Aug 1, 2015, but reported that they would do so for severe diarrhoea.
control_inclusion_criteria: Eligible cases were those aged 1 year and older on the fi rst day of the vaccination campaign who sought care for diarrhoea at all three cholera treatment centres and seven rehydration posts throughout Juba. Confirmed cases were suspected cases who tested positive to PCR for Vibrio cholerae O1.
non_case_confirmation_other: 5 refers to "Suspecte cases ... and who had not visited a health facility for diarrhoea before Aug 1, 2015, but reported that they would do so for severe diarrhoea."
f_source: Medecines sans frontieres

case_inclusion_criteria: Non-pregnant individuals older than 1 year residing in Kolkata. A diarrhoeal visit was defined as having, in the 24 h before presentation, at least three loose stools or (if one, two, or an indeterminate number of loose stools were reported) the patient must have shown evidence of some or severe dehydration according to WHO criteria. The primary endpoint, an episode of cholera for which a patient sought care at a health-care facility, was defined as a diarrhoeal episode in which no component visit was described as bloody, in which a fecal specimen yielded V cholerae O1, and the visit to treatment centre is confirmed
control_inclusion_criteria: Kolkata residents who are aged 1 year or older, were not pregnant, and provided written consent
f_source: Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation and the governments of South Korea, Sweden and Kuwait

case_inclusion_criteria: individuals with acute watery diarrhoea—defined as three or more loose, non-bloody, liquid stools in a 24-h period with an onset of 3 days or fewer before presentation—who sought treatment at any of the three study sites and met all eligibility criteria.
control_inclusion_criteria: Controls were matched by age group,residency and enrollment time. Controls were individuals who did not seek treatment for diarrhoea between the first day of study enrolment and the date of onset of symptoms in their corresponding case.
non_case_confirmation_other: Controls were individuals who did not seek treatment for diarrhoea between the first day of study enrolment and the date of onset of symptoms in their corresponding case.
f_source: National Institutes of Health, Delivering Oral Vaccines Eff ectively project, and Department of Global Health and Social Medicine at Harvard Medical School.

case_inclusion_criteria: All healthy, non-pregnant residents aged 2 years and older. A cholera episode is defined as acute non-bloody diarrhoea in a patient presenting for treatment whose faecal specimen yielded V cholerae O1.
control_inclusion_criteria: A cholera episode is defined as acute non-bloody diarrhoea in a patient presenting for treatment whose faecal specimen yielded V cholerae O1. All healthy, non-pregnant residents aged 2 years and older are eligible for the study.
f_source: Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency, and the South Korean Government.
study_l_comment: Cholera cases were detected in the study area starting from 7 to 14 months after the end of the vaccination campaign

case_inclusion_criteria: People with acute, nonbloody diarrhea severe enough to cause them to seek care at the Cholera Treatment Center between January 1 and May 31, 2004, were eligible if they gave written informed consent, had resided in study area since Dec 11, 2013, were at least 2 years of age, were not pregnant during the time of mass vaccination, were positive for V.cholerae O1, and their residence can be located after discharge for acquisition of information about vaccination and other data.
control_inclusion_criteria: Controls are neighbors matched by sex, age group and had not sought treatment for diarrhea at the Cholera Treatment Center between Dec 11 2003, and the onset of the matched case's diarrheal illness but would if severe, watery diarrhea had developed.
f_source: Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation
dose_delay_comment: The first round of immunization was conducted from December 11 to 20, 2003, and the second round from January 5 to 12, 2004, thus ensuring a minimum of 15 days between doses.

case_inclusion_criteria: All patients with suspected cholera (acute, nonbloody, watery diarrhea with more than 3 liquid stools in 24 hours)  who were seeking care in a health center in the study area between 1 week after the end of the vaccination campaigns and Oct 31,2012, provided written informed consents, and fulfilled the following criteria: they had resided in the study area since April16, 2012; they were 12months and older; they had a positive esult of rapid diagnostic test for cholera; and their residence could be located after discharge. Persons with repeated episodes of watery diarrhea during the study periods were included in the study only for the first episode.
control_inclusion_criteria: Controls were matched by sex, age group and residency, and was eligible if he or she had not sought treatment for diarrhea between Jan 1, 2012 and the date of onset of the matched case patient's diarheal illness and if he or she would have sought treatment in ahealth center if sevre, watery diarrhea had developed.
f_source: Medecines sans Frontieres
doses_l_comment: *vaccinatoin was considered incomplete if .....or one or both doses were spat out or vomited
doses_u_comment: *vaccinatoin was considered incomplete if .....or one or both doses were spat out or vomited

case_inclusion_criteria: A cholera episode was defined as a diarrhoeal episode with no passage of bloody stools, if a faecal specimen yielded V cholerae O1 or O139 and a follow-up check at home, done within 7 days of discharge, confi rmed that the participant had visited the treatment centre for diarrhoea on the recorded date of presentation.
control_inclusion_criteria: Non-pregnant residents aged 1 year and older in Dhaka Bangladesh
f_source: Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation
dose_delay_comment: The first dose was given between Feb 17, and April 16, 2011, and the second dose was given between March 15, and April 16, 2011.
study_l_comment: Followup period, not first or last day of cholera cases. // 14 days after the second dose for two-dose recipient.
study_u_comment: Followup period, not first or last day of cholera cases..716 days after the start of follow-up
general_comment: overall effectiveness

case_inclusion_criteria: Non-pregnant individuals older than 1 year residing in Kolkata. A diarrhoeal visit was defined as having, in the 24 h before presentation, at least three loose stools or (if one, two, or an indeterminate number of loose stools were reported) the patient must have shown evidence of some or severe dehydration according to WHO criteria. The primary endpoint, an episode of cholera for which a patient sought care at a health-care facility, was defined as a diarrhoeal episode in which no component visit was described as bloody, in which a fecal specimen yielded V cholerae O1, and the visit to treatment centre is confirmed
control_inclusion_criteria: Kolkata residents who are aged 1 year or older, were not pregnant, and provided written consent
f_source: Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency, Governments of South Korea, Sweden, and Kuwait.

case_inclusion_criteria: admitted to a polyclinic or hospital with diarrhoea and if a faecal sample obtained during the admission yielded V cholerae O1.
control_inclusion_criteria: Hue residents at least 1 years old. Controls were same age enumerated in the census and residing in an odd-numbered household.
f_source: Ministry of Health of Vietnam, the Swedish Agency for Research Cooperation with Developing Countries, the Global Program on Vaccines and Immunisation of the WHO, and the USA National Institute of Child Health and Human Development.

case_inclusion_criteria: admitted to a polyclinic or hospital with diarrhoea and if a faecal sample obtained during the admission yielded V cholerae O1. Cholera was classified as severe if the doctor who examined the patient at presentation judged the patient to have moderate or severe dehydration,7 or if the patient died while in hospital or polyclinic.

f_source: Ministry of Health of Vietnam, the Swedish Agency for Research Cooperation with Developing Countries, the Global Program on Vaccines and Immunisation of the WHO, and the USA National Institute of Child Health and Human Development.

case_inclusion_criteria: Patients were study site residents who sought treatment at one of five health care facilities, met the definition of diarrhea, gave informed consent, were listed in the census database, submitted a fecal specimen, and found positive for V. cholerae infection.
control_inclusion_criteria: patients seeking treatment for V. cholerae negative diarrhea. Controls were only selected during the length of cholera season.
biotype_majority_description: No dose specific data, 34/44 were El Tor
f_source: Thrasher Research Fund, Utah, USA
